The paper discusses methods for training autonomous vehicles using human demonstration and feedback, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on control and decision-making for autonomous vehicles suggests the categories of robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY) may also be relevant. Additionally, the paper mentions testing on lane-following, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) for autonomous vehicles.
